# AI Agent Workspace Rules

You are an AI assistant helping with this open-source project. You must strictly follow these workflow rules:

## 1. Registry Verification (CRITICAL)
- At the start of a session or task instruction, **you must ask the user** for their name, their selected role (Role 1 or Role 2), and which task from [TASKS.md](file:///c:/Users/anshul%20prajapati/OneDrive/Desktop/OPEN-SOURCE_FINDING_AI/TASKS.md) they want you to work on.
- Locate and read [TASKS.md](file:///c:/Users/anshul%20prajapati/OneDrive/Desktop/OPEN-SOURCE_FINDING_AI/TASKS.md).
- Ensure the user's name is entered under that task for their role. If it is empty or missing, write to [TASKS.md](file:///c:/Users/anshul%20prajapati/OneDrive/Desktop/OPEN-SOURCE_FINDING_AI/TASKS.md) to register the user's name/handle under that task before coding.
- This registry update and verification must also be completed manually by human contributors.

## 2. Modularity & File Separation Rule
- **NEVER** write multiple features or components in a single monolithic file.
- **ALWAYS** create a **new, separate file** for every new feature, sub-module, component, or helper function.
- Connect these files via explicit imports/exports.
- Do **NOT** merge files into a single unified file unless the user explicitly commands: *"make it in a single file now that the project is complete"*.

## 3. Role-Based Workflow
- **Role 1 (Feature Adder)**: Build feature logic in dedicated new files. When complete, update the task status in [TASKS.md](file:///c:/Users/anshul%20prajapati/OneDrive/Desktop/OPEN-SOURCE_FINDING_AI/TASKS.md) to indicate it is ready for Role 2.
- **Role 2 (Bug Fixer)**: Review the implementation of Role 1, fix any bugs/merging issues, update status to `Role 2 verification pending` when pushed, and finally to `Verified / Closed` once completely verified.

Refer to [AI_RULES.md](file:///c:/Users/anshul%20prajapati/OneDrive/Desktop/OPEN-SOURCE_FINDING_AI/AI_RULES.md) for full context and descriptions of these workflows.
